SUMMARY:Tri Kappa Exhibition ‚Äì Celebrating 125 Years
DESCRIPTION:Tri Kappa¬Ý125th Anniversary¬Ý\nOpening Exhibition Reception¬Ý\nBrown County Art Guild¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\nFebruary 22, 2026¬Ý¬Ý\n2-4pm / Remarks at 3pm¬Ý¬Ý\nCelebrate 125 years of Tri Kappa at the opening reception of a special exhibition drawn from the Tri Kappa Art Collection. Featuring works by Indiana artists, this exhibition honors Tri-Kappa‚Äôs long-standing commitment to the arts. Join us in celebrating the exhibition and Tri Kappa‚Äôs historic anniversary.¬Ý¬ÝLight refreshments will be served.¬Ý\nFree & open to the public.¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\n¬ÝTri¬ÝKappa¬Ý125th¬ÝAnniversary¬ÝExhibition¬Ý¬Ý\nFebruary 22 ‚Äì June 26, 2026¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\nBrown County Art Guild¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\n¬Ý\nJoin us in celebrating 125 years of Tri Kappa and its rich art collection.\nSince its¬Ýinception¬Ýin 1901, Tri Kappa has served as a cornerstone of Indiana‚Äôs cultural landscape, fostering a legacy of charity, culture, and education that spans generations. The Guild will¬Ýshowcase¬Ýa curated¬Ýselection¬Ýof paintings from the Tri-Kappa collection, highlighting the talents of Indiana artists, past and present. Discover works that reflect the beauty, creativity, and enduring spirit of our state‚Äôs artistic heritage.¬Ý\n\nBrown County Art Guild¬Ý‚Äì A not for profit organization¬Ýlocated¬Ýin the heart of downtown Nashville, Indiana.¬Ý¬ÝOn display throughout its galleries is a prized collection of historic paintings as well as current works for sale from regional award-winning member artists.¬Ý¬ÝThe Guild also offers artist demonstrations, workshops, and a variety of events or programs throughout the year.¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\nWinter Hours¬Ý‚Äì January¬Ý& February 2026, Monday-Wednesday¬Ýclosed or¬Ýby appt.~¬ÝThursday-Saturday, 11am-5pm¬Ý~¬ÝSunday, 12-4pm¬Ý¬Ý\nMarch ‚Äì December 2026, Monday ‚Äì Saturday 11am-5pm & Sundays 12-4pm¬Ý\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/tri-kappa-exhibition-celebrating-125-years/
ORGANIZER;CN=Brown County Art Guild:MAILTO:admin@bcartguild.org
CATEGORIES:Art Events &amp; Exhibits,Family Friendly,Free,Happening
LOCATION:Brown County Art Guild, South Van Buren Street, Nashville, IN
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://browncounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/J5UkpobD.jpg
END:VEVENT
