SUMMARY:Juneteenth Saturday Celebration at T.C. Steele
DESCRIPTION:At the T.C. Steele State Historic Site in Nashville, you can take a guided tour to explore the home and studio of Indiana‚Äôs most celebrated artist, surrounded by Brown County beauty. This is the perfect opportunity to see the centennial exhibition that commemorates the 100th anniversary of Steele‚Äôs death, featuring nearly 30 original works spanning Steele‚Äôs career and including rarely seen paintings and newly acquired pieces to the Indiana State Museum and Historic Sites‚Äô collection.\nGuided building tours are offered at 10:15 a.m., 1:15 p.m. and 3:15 p.m. Additionally, visitors can explore the site‚Äôs expansive natural surroundings, including the real locations that inspired Steele‚Äôs artworks. Tours are available on a first-come, first-served basis and advance registration is encouraged by calling¬Ý812.988.2785 ( tel:812.988.2785 ).\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/juneteenth-saturday-celebration-at-t-c-steele/
CATEGORIES:Art Events &amp; Exhibits,Free,Happening,Special Events
LOCATION:T.C. Steele State Historic Site, T C Steele Road, Nashville, IN
