SUMMARY:Painting Selma‚Äôs Garden
DESCRIPTION:\n\nFree admission\nStroll the grounds and watch as artists create their own interpretation of Selma‚Äôs garden during this fourth-annual event where admission is free.\nArtists interested in showcasing their talents to support this fundraising event can walk up on the day of the event to participate or contact Indiana Heritage Arts at¬Ý812-988-4609¬Ýfor additional information.\n5 ‚Äì 8 p.m. Reception\nTickets required\nVisitors can attend a¬Ýticketed reception¬Ýfeaturing food, wine and self-guided tours of the gardens and House of the Singing Winds, as well as a¬Ýwet paint art sale¬Ýin Steele‚Äôs large studio. Beginning at¬Ý6:15 p.m., enjoy a performance of the one-person play, ‚ÄúSelma and the Painter,‚Äù in the large studio. Tickets can be purchased via the blue button below.\nIf you are an artist wanting to register for the reception, please call¬ÝIndiana Heritage Arts at¬Ý812.988.2785.¬Ý\nPainting Selma‚Äôs Garden is supported by Brown County Community Foundation and presented in partnership with the Brown County Art Gallery and Indiana Heritage Arts.¬Ý\n\n\n\n\nTicketing Info\n\n\n\n\nAdmission to T.C. Steele State Historic Site from 10 a.m.-5 p.m. is free.\nThe evening reception requires tickets and is $40/person.¬Ý\n\n\n\n\n
