SUMMARY:Hindley Street Country Club
DESCRIPTION:Founded in 2017 by arranger / producer Constantine Delo, The Hindley Street Country Club (The HSCC) started as a group of Adelaide (South Australia) musicians, recording re-arranged covers and uploading them weekly to Facebook and YouTube. Fast forward to today, The HSCC has amassed over 590 million YouTube views with over 1 million subscribers globally and accumulated over 1 billion views across social media platforms. Following on from major internet success, The HSCC now tours throughout the world.\nThe Hindley Street Country Club is making waves around the globe. With a strong foundation in Australia and neighbouring New Zealand, the band captivated audiences in Southeast Asia in 2024, performing at prestigious events like the Singapore Grand Prix and in vibrant Manila, Philippines. Early 2025 saw them embark on a dynamic tour across the United States and Brazil, showcasing their exceptional talent and energy. Now, they are gearing up for an exciting new national tour in the U.S., alongside a highly anticipated summer tour in Eastern Europe and stops in the United Kingdom.\nHindley Street is located in the centre of Adelaide, and many musicians who have played with HSCC had gigs in bands up and down that street in the 1970s, ‚Äò80s and ‚Äò90s. The name is a play on the reputation of the street, which, in addition to pubs, clubs, amusement arcades, cinemas, fast food outlets and ice cream parlours, featured adult entertainment, tattoo shops, motorcycle gangs and a steady stream of traffic cruising up and down the strip. Hindley Street is an eclectic mix of activity today, including a university campus at one end. There is no actual ‚Äòcountry club‚Äô on Hindley Street in Adelaide, and the in-joke is mixing up a genteel concept like a country club with ‚ÄòHindley Street.‚Äô\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/hindley-street-country-club-2/
