SUMMARY:Ted Nugent
DESCRIPTION:Ted Nugent started ‚Äúbeating on my first guitar‚Äù around the age of five. Strongly influenced by Chuck Berry and Bo Diddly, he knew he wanted to pursue that type of sound and attitude. Early bands paved the way for the Amboy Dukes, and it was a feisty cover of the Dukes‚Äô psychedelic ‚ÄúJourney to the Center of the Mind‚Äù that kicked young Ted‚Äôs career into hyper drive.\nThe axe maniac broke out as a solo artist, signing with the legendary Epic Records, where the guitarist‚Äôs prodigious talent, ear-shattering volume and over-the-top stage antics quickly earned him the moniker of Motor City Madman. Cranking out hits like ‚ÄúCat Scratch Fever,‚Äù ‚ÄúJust What the Doctor Ordered,‚Äù ‚ÄúFree for All‚Äù and the iconic ‚ÄúStranglehold,‚Äù Nugent garnered international acclaim and earned a permanent place in rock & roll history as the ultimate guitar-shredding showman, selling more than 40 million albums and performing over 6,900 high-octane live shows. Ted Nugent has been named Detroit‚Äôs Greatest Guitar Player of All Time by readers of MLive.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/ted-nugent/
