SUMMARY:Blackhawk
DESCRIPTION:Renowned country music band BlackHawk, known for hits including ‚ÄúGoodbye Says It All,‚Äù ‚ÄúI Sure Can Smell the Rain,‚Äù ‚ÄúEvery Once in a While‚Äù and more, will perform live at the Brown County Music Center in Nashville, Ind., on Saturday, June 13, 2026.\nFor more than 20 years, BlackHawk has shared a unique sense of harmony with their voices, their songs and their fans. It‚Äôs a harmony that has sold over 7 million albums, scored some of the most distinctive country radio hits of the ‚Äò90s, and still draws tens of thousands of fans to their electrifying live performances. Today BlackHawk continues to honor its past as it forges its future, and does it all with a commitment that takes their music ‚Äì and the harmony ‚Äì to a whole new level.\nBlackHawk‚Äôs 1993 self-titled Arista debut album launched with the smash single ‚ÄúGoodbye Says It All,‚Äù followed by the Top 5 hits ‚ÄúEvery Once in a While,‚Äù ‚ÄúI Sure Can Smell the Rain,‚Äù ‚ÄúDown in Flames‚Äù and ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs Just About Right.‚Äù The album soon certified Double-Platinum, and the band received an ACM nomination as Best New Vocal Group Of The Year. BlackHawk followed up with the hit albums Strong Enough, Love & Gravity and Sky‚Äôs The Limit, which collectively featured such hits as ‚ÄúI‚Äôm Not Strong Enough To Say No,‚Äù ‚ÄúLike There Ain‚Äôt No Yesterday,‚Äù ‚ÄúBig Guitar,‚Äù ‚ÄúAlmost A Memory Now.‚Äù ‚ÄúThere You Have It‚Äù and ‚ÄúPostmarked Birmingham.‚Äù It was an unprecedented run of hits for a band that never quite fit the standard country mold.\nBlackHawk continues to record new music ‚Äì including their well-received 2015 Brothers Of The Southland album, a forthcoming Christmas record and an acoustic greatest hits album ‚Äì and deliver stellar live shows, backed by an all-star band of veteran country and southern rock players.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/blackhawk-2/
