TRANSP:OPAQUE
SUMMARY:Edwin McCain + Five For Fighting
DESCRIPTION:From Greenville, South Carolina, Edwin McCain is going on over 30 years of hits and worldwide touring. He has been called a ‚Äústreet corner prophet‚Äù by the USA Today, an ‚Äúaching tenor‚Äù by Slate Magazine, and a ‚Äúgreat American romantic‚Äù by the New York Times, but Edwin is much more than those things. After a long ride on a wave created by recording two of the biggest love songs in the history of music (‚ÄúI‚Äôll Be‚Äù and ‚ÄúI Could Not Ask For More‚Äù), and producing and starring in a tv series (‚ÄúFlippin‚Äô Ships‚Äù on Animal Planet); Edwin slowed his road schedule to dedicate more time to his primary roles as husband to his wife and father to their three young teenagers. His hit songs, authentic spirit and surprisingly affable sense of humor keeps everyone coming back time and time again. Well, the kids are grown-ish and Edwin‚Äôs fans are still clamoring for more. Not that Edwin‚Äôs music ever slows down. ‚ÄúAmerican Idol‚Äù and ‚ÄúThe Voice‚Äù contestants still turn to Edwin‚Äôs ballads year after year to help them win over judges and fans. Edwins shares, ‚ÄúThe 15-year-old me would have crawled through a river of fire to be the singer/songwriter that I am today, and I remember that. I am incredibly grateful to be able to do this.‚Äù Millions more have been turned on by pop icons Justin Bieber and Charlie Puth who have both covered Edwin‚Äôs hit songs. Edwin McCain will be touring everywhere in 2024. We‚Äôll see you on the road!\nIn the two decades since his first major single ‚ÄúSuperman (It‚Äôs Not Easy)‚Äù hit the stratosphere, John Ondrasik ‚Äì the songwriter and performer known as the platinum-selling, Grammy-nominated, Five For Fighting ‚Äì has both evolved and come back ‚Äòround full circle. To date, Five For Fighting, has released six studio LPs, including the platinum certified America Town and The Battle for Everything; and the top-10 charting Two Lights, along with an EP and live albums. Ondrasik has penned major hits, including the chart-topping ‚Äú100 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Riddle,‚Äù ‚ÄúChances,‚Äù ‚ÄúWorld,‚Äù and ‚ÄúEasy Tonight,‚Äù which have earned over one billion streams and place him as a top-10 Hot Adult Contemporary artist for the 2000s. The reflective ‚Äú100 Years‚Äù has joined ‚ÄúSuperman (It‚Äôs Not Easy)‚Äù as part of the American Songbook and continues to stand the test of time at weddings, birthdays, graduations, memorials, and many a home video. Five For Fighting‚Äôs music has also been featured in more than 350 films, television shows, and commercials, including the Oscar-winning The Blind Side, Hawaii Five-O, The Sopranos and the CBS drama, Code Black.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/edwin-mccain-five-for-fighting-2/
