SUMMARY:The Oak Ridge Boys
DESCRIPTION:One of the most renowned ‚Äúlegacy acts‚Äù of all time with a 50-year string of hits, The Oak Ridge Boys return to the Brown County Music Center in Nashville, Ind., on Thursday, June 4, 2026.\nTheirs is one of the most distinctive and recognizable sounds in the music industry. The four-part harmonies and upbeat songs of The Oak Ridge Boys have spawned dozens of Country hits and two Pop smashes, earned them Grammy, Dove, CMA, and ACM awards and garnered a host of other industry and fan accolades. Every time they step before an audience, the Oaks bring four decades of charted singles, and 50 years of tradition, to a stage show widely acknowledged as among the most exciting anywhere. And each remains as enthusiastic about the process as they have ever been.\nLead singer Duane Allen, bass singer extraordinaire Richard Sterban, tenor Joe Bonsall and baritone William Lee Golden comprise one of Country‚Äôs truly legendary acts. Their string of hits includes the Country-Pop chartbuster ‚ÄúElvira,‚Äù as well as ‚ÄúBobbie Sue,‚Äù ‚ÄúDream On,‚Äù ‚ÄúThank God For Kids,‚Äù ‚ÄúAmerican Made,‚Äù ‚ÄúI Guess It Never Hurts To Hurt Sometimes,‚Äù ‚ÄúFancy Free,‚Äù Gonna Take A Lot Of River,‚Äù and many others. In 2009, they covered a White Stripes song, receiving accolades from Rock reviewers. In 2011, they rerecorded a 30th anniversary version of ‚ÄúElvira‚Äù for a Cracker Barrel Old Country Store project. The group has scored 12 gold, three platinum, and one double platinum album‚Äîplus one double platinum single‚Äîand had more than a dozen national Number One singles and over 30 Top Ten hits.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/the-oak-ridge-boys-2/
