SUMMARY:2026 Barn Sale
DESCRIPTION:Donation Days ‚Äì we will gladly accept donations of new and gently used items on the following dates:\nFriday, August 7\nSaturday, August 8\nSunday, August 9\n9am to 4pm\nVolunteers needed!! We need volunteers to help prepare the donated items (cleaning, sorting, pricing, etc.) as well as individuals to help with heavy lifting to move and arrange larger donated items.¬Ý Dates help is needed are Aug 7 through Aug 16. If you would be interested in helping, reach out to Megan Gushwa at volunteer@bchumane.org or call/text 317-946-8235.\nWhat type of donations are we looking for? Just look around your house and see what you‚Äôre no longer using. We accept:\n\nAntiques and collectibles\nFurniture, lamps, and rugs\nToys and baby items\nJewelry\nKnick knacks\nKitchen appliances\nHousewares\nTools and gardening equipment\nSports gear\nOutdoor supplies\nPicture frames and artwork\nCraft and Hobby Items\nHoliday decorations\nBoats\n‚Ä¶and more!\n\nIf you‚Äôre not using it, someone else can!\nWe are unable to accept clothes, shoes, candles, food, personal hygiene items, mattresses, cribs, car seats, sofa sleepers, tube TVs, older computers and electronics, older exercise equipment, file cabinets, cassette tapes, VHS tapes, pianos/organs, fuel-powered heaters, large entertainment centers or items that are not in working order.\nThen, come back and enjoy the sale.¬ÝIt‚Äôs the biggest yard sale of the year, with¬Ýthousands¬Ýof items available. All of the money goes to support the animals at the shelter.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/2026-barn-sale/
