SUMMARY:Shelby Spring Fling
DESCRIPTION:Witness automotive history as vintage Shelbys, Mustangs, and Ford-powered classics roll into Brown County for the annual Shelby Spring Fling, happening May 16-17 at Brown County State Park! A Brown County tradition since 1977, this longtime gathering brings together car enthusiasts from across the Midwest for a weekend filled with classic cars, community, and scenic cruising through the hills of Brown County.\nSaturday‚Äôs featured car show takes place in the pool parking area just through the North Gate and includes dozens of classes of vintage and modern performance vehicles. Whether you‚Äôre a lifelong enthusiast or simply curious to check out some incredible cars, everyone is welcome to stop by and enjoy the show.\n
