SUMMARY:Chamberfest Brown County: Letters From The Front
DESCRIPTION:\n\n\n\n\nIntroducing New Music Celebrating History And Honoring Service\nLetters From The Front¬Ýis a new musical work for four voices and piano. Composed by New York composer Patrick Zimmerli with libretto by Mirabelle Ordinaire, this song cycle is based on letters sent by service members and their loved ones during wartime. Each piece is based on an actual letter written during one of our nation‚Äôs most crucial wars, including the American Revolution, the Civil War, World War I, World War II, Vietnam, and the Gulf War.\nThis new work will be released in the summer of 2026 to celebrate the 250th birthday of the United States.\n\n\n\n\n\nFeaturing:¬Ý\n\n\nANGELA BORN ‚Äì MEZZO-SOPRANO\n\n\nDAVID GOVERTSEN ‚Äì BASS-BARITONE\n\n\nDESIR√âE HASSLER ‚Äì SOPRANO\n\n\nTYLER LEE ‚Äì TENOR\n\n\nLAN GINDES ‚Äì PIANO\n\n\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/chamberfest-brown-county-letters-from-the-front/
