SUMMARY:Dead Letter Office: A Tribute to R.E.M.
DESCRIPTION:Dead Letter Office have dedicated themselves to faithfully reproducing the music and energy of a live R.E.M. show. Since 2014, Dead Letter Office has been thrilling audiences throughout the U.S. & Canada, providing a show that‚Äôs been sorely missed since R.E.M called it quits.\nDead Letter Office not only performs R.E.M.‚Äôs major hits but also dives deep into their catalog to please the die-hard fans!\nDead Letter Office has also been joined onstage by members of R.E.M.!! Mike Mills joined them on stage in Buffalo, NY for Man on the Moon. Peter Buck joined them onstage at Clusterfest in San Francisco, CA (in front of 8000 people) for Sitting Still and So. Central Rain!\n‚ÄúI think we can unequivocally say that ‚ÄòYou are the Best [R.E.M. tribute]‚Äô‚Äù ‚Äì Adam Scott, actor (Parks and Recreation), and uber R.E.M. fan\n‚ÄúYou guys were terrific, nothing short of mesmerizing. I‚Äôll be first in line for your return show!!‚Äù ‚Äì Patton Biddle, R.E.M.‚Äôs sound man in early days\n‚Äú[An] excellent R.E.M. tribute band.‚Äù ‚Äì Rob Sheffield, Contributing Writer, Rolling Stone\n‚Äú[The] greatest R.E.M. tribute band is called Dead Letter Office, and they rule. If they come to your town, go.‚Äù ‚Äì Patrick Hosken, @MTVNews and @Billboard\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/dead-letter-office-a-tribute-to-r-e-m/
