SUMMARY:Moon Over Buffalo [Live Theatre]
DESCRIPTION:It is the summer of 1953, and George and Charlotte Hay, former Broadway stars, have taken their run-down touring company to Buffalo, New York. In Buffalo they have the intention of running ‚ÄúCyrano de Bergerac‚Äù and ‚ÄúPrivate Lives‚Äù in repertory, all the while grumbling about missed Hollywood opportunities. But on-stage harmony is compromised when George performs an off-stage infidelity, impregnating the company‚Äôs ingenue. When Charlotte learns of this, she prepares to run away with the family lawyer, sending lightweight George on a grief-stricken drinking binge. Meanwhile, it ¬Ýturns out that Frank Capra is headed to town on a talent scouting mission looking to hire the couple for his swashbuckling Scarlet Pimpernel epic. As a result, the Hay family ‚Äî including scornful, deaf mother-in-law Ethel, determinedly practical daughter Rosalind, and dashing actor Paul, Rosalind‚Äôs ex-boyfriend ‚Äî must work overtime to get sloppy drunk George into his Cyrano hat and nose‚Ä¶. or is it his Elyot Chase smoking jacket? With the entrance of Rosalind‚Äôs fianc√©, anxious TV weatherman Howard ‚Äî one man with two mistaken identities ‚Äî and Richard Maynard, the wealthy lawyer hoping to lure Charlotte away to his mansion ‚Äî the confusion only intensifies.\n¬Ý\nCAST & CREW\nGeorge: Ed Phillips\nPaul: Brenden King\nHoward: Larry Compton\nRichard: Tim Staggs\nCharlotte: Kristy Kelly\nRosalind: Dania Leova\nEileen: Erin Rudich\nEthel: Sheila Popplewell\nDirector: Steve Booker\nAssistant Director: Wendi Gore\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/moon-over-buffalo-live-theatre/
