SUMMARY:Blue October
DESCRIPTION:Twenty years after the album that launched them into the global spotlight, Blue October celebrates the anniversary of their platinum-selling record Foiled with a global tour including a return to the Brown County Music Center in Nashville, Ind., on Sunday, November 8, 2026. The band will also release a special vinyl reissue, arriving May 29 via Universal Music.\nBlue October‚Äôs deeply personal songwriting and emotionally resonant sound on Foiled cemented the Houston-bred band as one of rock‚Äôs most distinctive voices. While Foiled marked a breakthrough moment for the band, it was only the beginning. Its impact continues to ripple¬Ý outward as new listeners discover the album alongside the expansive catalog that followed. The¬Ý connection forged through its lyrics has only deepened over time, helping grow a devoted global audience. Blue October‚Äôs catalog now surpasses one billion streams and continues to climb.\nThe album initially sent frontman Justin Furstenfeld and Blue October‚Äôs life into a whirlwind,¬Ý now, as the singer looks back on it 20 years in the rearview, and particularly as the band prepares¬Ý to launch a yearlong Foiled 20th-anniversary celebration, he has come to realize what a true¬Ý blessing his band‚Äôs most beloved body of work has been in his life. Furstenfeld wrote the songs during an intensely personal period while living alone in Los Angeles,¬Ý first capturing them as raw demos that reflected the vulnerability behind the record. Produced by¬Ý Furstenfeld and David Castell, the 14-track collection balances deeply confessional lyrics with¬Ý soaring melodies and emotional honesty that became a hallmark.\nCracking the Billboard Rock Chart Top 10, Foiled remains a cornerstone of alternative rock,¬Ý anchored by Billboard-charting hits, including the platinum-certified ‚ÄúHate Me,‚Äù ‚ÄúInto the Ocean‚Äù and fan favorite ‚ÄúShe‚Äôs My Ride Home.‚Äù\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/blue-october/
CATEGORIES:Entertainment,Happening,Live Music
LOCATION:200 Maple Leaf Boulevard, Nashville, IN 47448
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://browncounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Music-Center.jpg
