SUMMARY:Dawg Gone Walk & Fiesta
DESCRIPTION:Brown County Humane Society creates an afternoon of Dawg-gone fun for humans and their furry canine companions. We have games, contests, pampering stations, information booths, and even shopping!\nFunds raised for the event go directly to the feeding and care of homeless pets at the shelter. This helps us maintain and improve our amazing 98% save rate, one of the nation‚Äôs best.\nCome out and join the fun.\nPLUS:¬ÝThe first 125 people to register get a free goody bag\nSponsors and vendors are being accepted for this year‚Äôs event. Read more about how you can participate by clicking here. ( https://www.bchumane.org/dawg-gone-walk-fiesta-sponsorship-vendor-information/ )\nThe male dog and female dog (and their owners) that raise the most in donations will win our coveted King & Queen baskets. These baskets include goodies for both the dog and their human and is valued at over $150 each! The more you raise, the better your chances of winning. Learn more and register your dog today at:¬Ýhttps://givebutter.com/king-and-queen-of-the-party-2026 ( https://givebutter.com/king-and-queen-of-the-party-2026 ).\nIf you cannot attend the Dawg Gone Walk & Fiesta but still want to support the shelter or a dog in your life ‚Äì the King and Queen contest is a great way to do that! You can donate to any dog‚Äôs campaign, and the proceeds will help them get that much closer to the crown at this year‚Äôs event.¬Ý Attendance is not required to support this campaign.\nNote:\n~¬ÝEvent is held rain or shine. No refunds will be given for inclement weather.\n~ All dogs must be leashed.\n~ Dogs must enjoy the company of other dogs and people.\n~ Dogs must be current on vaccinations.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/dawg-gone-walk-fiesta/
