SUMMARY:Brown County Art Guild 2026 Annual Raffle
DESCRIPTION:Take a chance to win ‚ÄòPainters Point‚Äô, a beautiful original oil painting generously donated by Guild Artist, Allen Hutton. He strives to¬Ýrender¬Ýthe fleeting patterns of light and shadow with the simple purpose of preserving the reality of a landscape at a particular moment in time and season. Allen has achieved¬Ýnumerous¬Ýawards¬Ýand his art can be found in both private and corporate collections across the county.¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\nTickets:¬Ý 1 for $30, 2 for $50, or 5 for $100¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\nYour generosity helps the Guild to preserve its historic collection, promote its award-winning artist members, and offer workshops and programs throughout the year!¬Ý¬Ý\nThe drawing of the winning raffle ticket will be held at 3pm on Saturday, November 21, 2026, at the Guild.¬Ý¬Ý\nThe winner need not be present for the drawing.¬Ý¬Ý\nPurchase options:¬Ý\nIn person at the Guild, call 812-988-6185 or purchase raffle tickets at:¬Ý¬Ý\nhttps://browncountyartguild.org/product/brown-county-art-guild-annual-raffle/¬Ý\n‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî-¬Ý\nBrown County Art Guild¬Ý‚Äì¬ÝPO Box 324 ‚Äì 48 S. Van Buren St. Nashville, Indiana¬Ý47448¬Ý‚Äì¬ÝPh#¬Ý812-988-6185¬Ý\n‚Äì A¬Ýnot-for-profit¬Ýorganization¬Ýlocated¬Ýin the heart of downtown Nashville, Indiana. On display throughout its galleries is a prized collection of historic paintings as well as current works for sale from regional award-winning member artists.¬Ý¬ÝThroughout the year, the¬ÝGuild offers¬Ýartist demonstrations, workshops, and special exhibits.¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\nGuild hours: March-December 2026, Monday ‚Äì Saturday, 11 ‚Äì 5 and Sunday, 12 ‚Äì 4 or by appointment.¬Ý\n
