SUMMARY:Brown County Lions Club Independence Day Fireworks Display
DESCRIPTION:The Brown County Lions Club¬Ýannounced America‚Äôs best¬ÝSmall Town¬ÝFireworks is moving locations in 2026. The show has traditionally been held over the Brown County High School football field, but is moving to its¬Ýnew home at Eagle Park, just¬Ýwest of the north entrance to Brown County State Park.¬ÝThis year‚Äôs show is¬Ýset for¬ÝThursday, July 2, 2026.¬ÝMapping apps will recognize ‚ÄúEagle Park¬ÝNashville¬ÝIndiana.‚Äù¬Ý\nFor more than¬Ý50 years, the Brown County Lions Club has proudly presented this annual Independence Day tradition, honoring the nation with a spectacular fireworks show that has become a highlight of summer in Brown County.¬Ý\nThe fireworks will begin¬Ýat dark¬Ýand¬Ýthere will be plenty of parking available at Eagle Park. Attendees are encouraged to bring lawn chairs or blankets.¬Ý¬Ý¬Ý\nAdding to the community spirit of the evening,¬ÝScouts from Troop 190¬Ýwill be on site selling food and glow bracelets, with proceeds helping scouts earn money for summer camp.¬Ý¬Ý\nThe Independence Day fireworks are made possible entirely through the generosity of the community. The show is funded by¬Ýdonations from local small businesses¬Ýand contributions collected by¬ÝThe Bucket Brigade,¬ÝLions Club members¬Ýwho¬Ýcirculate through the crowd¬Ýbefore the show.¬Ý\n
