SUMMARY:Paper & Fabric Marbling with Hannah Hadley
DESCRIPTION:Paper & Fabric Marbling with Hannah Hadley\nExploring Color, Meditative Flow, and Ancient Technique\nJoin Indianapolis artist Hannah Hadley for a hands-on marbling workshop that brings the mesmerizing art of marbling to both paper and fabric. Rooted in centuries-old tradition, marbling is a playful and meditative process where color dances on the surface of water before being transferred to paper or cloth‚Äîeach piece entirely one of a kind.\nIn this class, you‚Äôll learn the fundamentals of marbling and create your own vibrant marbled paper and fabric samples. You‚Äôll explore color mixing, pattern-making techniques, and how to work with different materials to achieve beautiful, flowing results.\nHannah brings her deep love of craft and connection to the natural world into every class. As a practicing artist and experienced teacher in sewing, natural dyeing, marbling, and felting, she‚Äôll guide you in discovering how marbling can be both joyful and grounding.\nWhether you‚Äôre a total beginner or a seasoned maker, this class invites you to slow down, connect, and leave with a collection of luminous, marbled creations.\nAll materials provided. No experience necessary.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/paper-fabric-marbling-with-hannah-hadley/
CATEGORIES:Art Events &amp; Exhibits,Classes &amp; Workshops,Happening
LOCATION:61 West Main Street, Nashville, IN
