SUMMARY:Uncle Pen Fest
DESCRIPTION:Various bluegrass performers, workshops, and jams plus the Bluegrass Hall of Fame Induction.\nFounded in 1974, Uncle Pen Days began as a tribute to Bill Monroe‚Äôs maternal uncle, James Pendleton Vandiver. ‚ÄúUncle Pen‚Äù played the fiddle and Monroe later said that he was the ‚Äúfellow that I learned to play from.‚Äù Bill Monroe‚Äôs parents had both died by the time he was 16, and Monroe lived part of the time this his uncle, where he would play mandolin while his uncle played fiddle at local square dances and social events.\nGreatly influenced by Vandiver, Bill Monroe wrote a song about him, Uncle Pen, in 1950 ‚Äî a song that went on to be a hit for Porter Wagoner (1954) and Ricky Skaggs (1984).\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/uncle-pen-fest/
