SUMMARY:Phoenix: Saxophone Quartet
DESCRIPTION:ChamberFest Brown County presents Phoenix: Saxophone Quartet\n‚Äã‚ÄãThe multi-award-winning Project Fusion Sax Quartet presents Phoenix: a program of saxophone chamber music depicting renewal, transformation, and flight. This theme, chosen in the auspicious year of the United States‚Äô 250th anniversary, celebrates a nation founded on the ‚Äúgreat experiment‚Äù of democratic reinvention and rebirth, whose mascot is fittingly the noble bald eagle: as such, it presents music exclusively of American composers.\nWorks by Gershwin, Maslanka, Kline, Frazier, Mettens, Washington, Ge, Love\nProject Fusion:\n\nDannel Espinoza, soprano sax\nDoug O‚ÄôConnor, alto sax\nAiwen Zhang, tenor sax\nMatt Evans, baritone sax\n\nThis concert is sponsored by the Eads family in memory of Ralph S. (Tony) Eads.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/chamberfest-phoenix/
