SUMMARY:Adult-ish Camp
DESCRIPTION:Adult-ish Camp is the perfect chance to relive the magic of summer camp ‚Äì this time with the freedom of adulthood! Designed for young adults ages 18+, this long weekend at Waycross is all about fun, reflection, and connection. Spend your days canoeing, hiking, and enjoying campfires, or simply relax and soak in the peaceful surroundings. Whether you‚Äôre seeking adventure or just a break from the daily grind, you can participate as much or as little as you‚Äôd like.\nThis program will offer a space to reflect on the transitions of young adulthood. With a mix of classic camp activities and opportunities for reflection, it‚Äôs a chance to step away from routine and connect with like-minded people. If you‚Äôre ready for a weekend of fun, friendship, and nostalgia, this is the camp for you!\n\n\nJuly 31-August 3, 2026\n\n\nCheck-in: 4-6pm\n\n\nCheck-out: 10am\n\n\nThis program runs Friday ‚Äì Monday. We encourage all participants to stay for the full experience, but we understand that some may need to leave early. If you need to depart early please select the Friday‚ÄìSunday afternoon option (departing before dinner on Sunday) during registration so we can plan accordingly.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAge: Young Adults (18+)\n\n\nAccommodation Options:\n\n\nAttendance cost is calculated during online registration, depending on your lodging selection. Rates are per person and include program fees, lodging and meals\n\n\nCabin ‚Äì Multi-Occupancy: $75 per person\n\n\nMain House/Sleeping Wing Multi-Occupancy: $75 per person\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
